cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper involves the use of deep learning for motion analysis of medical images, specifically cardiac magnetic resonance imaging, and the prediction of human survival. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of a supervised denoising autoencoder, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a neural network also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of medical images, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
